    <body>
        <section id="introduction">
            <h1>IntelliSense Features</h1>
            <p>This document demonstrates context-sensitive IntelliSense functionality.</p>
            <p>When you type &lt; inside different elements, you'll see different suggestions:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Inside &lt;body&gt;: section, article, aside</li>
                <li>Inside &lt;section&gt;: h1, h2, h3, p, ul, ol</li>
                <li>Inside &lt;ul&gt;: li</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <article id="features">
            <h2>Key Features</h2>
            <p>Context-sensitive element suggestions based on XSD schema.</p>
            <p>Automatic tag closing when typing &gt;.</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Type &lt; to trigger IntelliSense</li>
                <li>Use ↑/↓ to navigate suggestions</li>
                <li>Press ENTER to select an element</li>
                <li>Type &gt; to auto-close the tag</li>
            </ol>
        </article>

        <aside>
            <h2>Tips</h2>
            <p>Make sure to load the corresponding XSD schema for best results.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Load XSD file in the XML Editor</li>
                <li>Element names are automatically extracted</li>
                <li>Context is determined by current cursor position</li>
            </ul>
        </aside>
